criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. meet the diagnostic criteria of chronic tic disorder or tourette syndrome;

          2. YGTSS score is greater than 20;

          3. the symptoms lasted more than 1 year, and the drug regimen was not adjusted within one
             month;

          4. right-handedness;

          5. age 6-64 years;

          6. able to receive TMS therapy, participants and their guardians agree to receive
             treatment and observation.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. age is under 6-year old;

          2. can not tolerate MRI or TMS treatment;

          3. adjust medication during treatment.
